Q: How to clone the repo?
SSH> git clone git@54.243.245.108:~/reciprocity-ring.git

Q: How to checkout an empty repo and make a first checkin?
The first git push always require to specify the branch you want to push.
git push -u origin master
Then the next push can be done, from the same branch, as you intended:
git push

Q: How to add a new repository?
server:
ssh git@<git_ip>
mkdir helpedite.git
git init helpedite.git

client:
git clone git@<git_server>:/helpedite.git

